// AesNiEightEnc i386 (merged key sizes)
// Define exactly one of: CRYPTOLIB_AESNI_KEY128, CRYPTOLIB_AESNI_KEY192, CRYPTOLIB_AESNI_KEY256
// before including this file (see ClpAesEngineX86).
//
// True 8-wide AES-NI encrypt, in-place. ebx=state (8*16 bytes), esi=keys.
// xmm0..xmm7 hold the 8 data blocks; round keys consumed as memory operands.
// Memory-operand form is used because i386 has no xmm8+, so we cannot stash the
// shared round key without losing a data register. Round-key reads are naturally
// coalesced by modern CPUs (same line, same cycle).
// AES-NI instructions are db-encoded for broad assembler compatibility.

